        "title": "Casting Object to Object[][]",
        "body": "<p>I need to cast an object into a multidimensional array but can't figure out how to do it. The object might contain an array of any object (boolean[][], int[][], String[][] etc). Here is a sample code:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public static void main(String[] args) {\n    boolean[][] b = new boolean[10][10];\n\n    Object o = b;\n\n    Object[][] multiArray = (Object[][])o;\n\n    for(int i = 0; i &lt; multiArray.length; i++) {\n        for(int j = 0; j &lt; multiArray[i].length; j++) {\n            // Do something\n        }\n    }\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
        "question_id": 17095367,
